cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.RO

This paper is about improving information flow in neural networks for instance segmentation, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a new network architecture, which involves enhancing feature hierarchy and creating a complementary branch, indicating that it may also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper mentions adaptive feature pooling and bottom-up path augmentation, which are techniques commonly used in deep learning and artificial intelligence, suggesting that it could also fit into cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper mentions the COCO 2017 Challenge Instance Segmentation task, which is related to robotics and autonomous systems, indicating that it could also be classified as cs.RO (Robotics).
